The media manager component lets you upload and insert images into content throughout your site. Optionally

'core_content_id': <hr title="Extensions Manager" alt="Extensions Manager" class="system-pagebreak" style="color: gray; border: 1px dashed gray;" />

'core_content_id': <hr title="Menu Manager" alt="Menu Manager" class="system-pagebreak" style="color: gray; border: 1px dashed gray;" />
The menu manager lets you create the menus you see displayed on your site. It also allows you to assign modules and template styles to specific menu links. Help
<hr title="Global Configuration" alt="Global Configuration" class="system-pagebreak" style="color: gray; border: 1px dashed gray;" />
The global configuration is where the site administrator configures things such as whether search engine friendly urls are enabled
'core_type_alias': the site meta data (descriptive text used by search engines and indexers) and other functions. For many beginning users simply leaving the settings on default is a good way to begin
'core_title': although when your site is ready for the public you will want to change the meta data to match its content. Help

'core_content_id': <hr title="Banners" alt="Banners" class="system-pagebreak" style="color: gray; border: 1px dashed gray;" />
The banners component provides a simple way to display a rotating image in a module and
'core_type_alias': if you wish to have advertising
'core_title': a way to track the number of times an image is viewed and clicked. Help

'core_content_id':
The redirect component is used to manage broken links that produce Page Not Found (404) errors. If enabled it will allow you to redirect broken links to specific pages. It can also be used to manage migration related URL changes. Help

Welcome to the Fruit Shop

'core_content_id': We sell fruits from around the world. Please use our website to learn more about our business. We hope you will come to our shop and buy some fruit.
This mini site will show you how you might want to set up a site for a business

'core_title': you might want to extend it with e-commerce

'core_state': many of which are available through the Joomla! Extensions Directory.

 There are lots of places you can get help with Joomla!. In many places in your site administrator you will see the help icon. Click on this for more information about the options and functions of items on your screen. Other places to get help are:

'

It\'s easy to get started creating your website. Knowing some of the basics will help.

'core_content_id': A content management system is software that allows you to create and manage webpages easily by separating the creation of your content from the mechanics required to present it on the web.

'core_type_alias': the content is stored in a database. The look and feel are created by a template. The Joomla! software brings together the template and the content to create web pages.

'core_content_id': Your site actually has two separate sites. The site (also called the front end) is what visitors to your site will see. The administrator (also called the back end) is only used by people managing your site. You can access the administrator by clicking the "Site Administrator" link on the "This Site" menu or by adding /administrator to the end of you domain name.
Log in to the administrator using the username and password created during the installation of Joomla.

To login to the front end of your site use the login form or the login menu link on the "This Site" menu. Use the user name and password that were created as part of the installation process. Once logged-in you will be able to create and edit articles.

'core_type_alias': you will be able to create content that only logged-in users are able to see.
a new menu will be visible. To create a new article
'core_title': click on the "submit article" link on that menu.

'core_content_id': The new article interface gives you a lot of options
'core_type_alias': but all you need to do is add a title and put something in the content area. To make it easy to find
'core_title': set the state to published and put it in the Joomla category.

'core_content_id': You can edit an existing article by clicking on the edit icon (this only displays to users who have the right to edit).

There is much more to learn about how to use Joomla! to create the website you envision. You can learn much more at the Joomla! documentation site and on the Joomla! forums.

'

As you make your Joomla! site you will control the details of the display using options also referred to as parameters. Options control everything from whether the author\'s name is displayed to who can view what to the number of items shown on a list.

'core_content_id': Default options for each component are changed using the Options button on the component toolbar.
Options can also be set on an individual item
'core_type_alias': such as an article or contact and in menu links.

'core_content_id': If you are happy with how your site looks
'core_type_alias': it is fine to leave all of the options set to the defaults that were created when your site was installed. As you become more experienced with Joomla you will use options more.

Joomla! 2.5 offers two search options.

'core_content_id': The Basic Search component provides basic search functionality for the information contained in your core components. Many extensions can also be searched by the search component. Help
The Smart Search component offers searching similar to that found in major search engines. Smart Search is disabled by default. If you choose to enable it you will need to take several steps. First
'core_type_alias': enable the Smart Search Plugin in the plugin manager. Then
'core_title': if you are using the Basic Search Module replace it with the Smart Search Module. Finally
'core_alias': if you have already created content

Joomla means All Together
'core_state': and it is a community of people all working and having fun together that makes Joomla possible. Thousands of people each year participate in the Joomla community

'core_type_alias': of all skill levels and from around the world are welcome to join in. Participate in the Joomla.org family of websites (the forum is a great place to start). Come to a Joomla! event. Join or start a Joomla! Users Group. Whether you are a developer

The Joomla Project consists of all of the people who make and support the Joomla Web Platform and Content Management System.

'core_content_id': Our mission is to provide a flexible platform for digital publishing and collaboration.
• People publishing and collaborating in their communities and around the world
• A community that is enjoyable and rewarding to participate in
• People around the world using their preferred languages
• A project dedicated to maintaining the trust of its users
There are millions of users around the world and thousands of people who contribute to the Joomla Project. They work in three main groups: the Production Working Group
'core_type_alias': responsible for everything that goes into software and documentation; the Community Working Group
'core_title': responsible for creating a nurturing the community; and Open Source Matters
'core_alias': the non profit organization responsible for managing legal
'core_body': financial and organizational issues.

'core_content_id': Joomla is a free and open source project
'core_type_alias':
which uses the GNU General Public License version 2 or later.
